CHAT.comment: Home Visit 5; Chi sits on Mot's lap while his sister kneels by them and looks on
Book Reading; The Very Hungry Caterpillar

Chi is not a very strong reader , but with a lot of support and sounding out from Mot , he is able to read many words. Mot's cues include providing words , giving first sounds or syllables , and a few times she points to the picture. Chi is not completely unaware of what the story is. For example , he notes that the caterpillar is <super hungry>. For the most part , Chi's reading consists of echoing words given by his mother. Chi also uses contextual cues , as shown by his reading words like leaf and caterpillar where they don't appear in the text.
